        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 4:52PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 452 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hinckley, or 8 miles northwest of Plano, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Montgomery, Valley View, Elburn, North Aurora, Geneva, Big Rock,
Kaneville, Aurora, Batavia, St. Charles, Hinckley, Sugar Grove,
Little Rock, Wayne, South Elgin, Campton Hills, and Yorkville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
